 BY MAYOWA SAMUEL Gunmen have kidnapped the chairman of the Christian Association of Nigeria (CAN) in Jos East Local Government Area of Plateau State, Rev James Kantoma. Reports have it that  the Priest of St Anthony Parish in Angware community, was abducted at his house on Monday morning . Confirming the abduction of the cleric, Plateau CAN Chairman, Polycarp Lubo said: “Since the gunmen took the Reverend Father away, we have not heard anything either from him or the abductors up till this afternoon. “This is so sad. But we are praying for him that no harm will befall him wherever he is.” A resident of the community, Paul Aware, also confirmed the abduction of the Reverend father to reporters in Jos on Monday.